winRate = []
first_pokemon = battles['First_pokemon']
second_pokemon = battles['Second_pokemon']
winner = battles['Winner']

for index, row in pokemons.iterrows():
    wins = np.sum(winner == row['#'])
    total = np.sum(first_pokemon == row['#']) + np.sum(second_pokemon == row['#'])
    winRate.append(0 if total == 0 else wins / total) # 0% win rate if no battle record

# This is the result for [Q1]
pokemons['WinRate'] = winRate

train, val = train_test_split(pokemons, test_size=0.2, random_state=4211)

models = []
features = ['HP', 'Attack', 'Defense', 'Sp. Atk', 'Sp. Def', 'Speed']
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))

def reshape_feature(x):
    return x.values.reshape(-1, 1)

for idx, feature in enumerate(features):
    X_train = reshape_feature(train[feature])
    X_val = reshape_feature(val[feature])
    
    clf = LinearRegression()
    clf.fit(X_train, train['WinRate'])
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_val)
    # This is the result for [Q2]
    print('R2 socre of %s:  \t%f' % (feature, r2_score(val['WinRate'], y_pred)))
    
    # These are the result for [Q3]
    plt.subplot(2, 3, idx + 1)
    plt.scatter(X_val, reshape_feature(val['WinRate']))
    plt.plot(X_val, y_pred, color='red')
    plt.title('WinRate vs %s' % feature)
    plt.xlabel(feature)
    plt.ylabel('WinRate')
    
    models.append(clf)

# These are the variable and functions that will use in the whole Task 3 and Task 4

model_sample_size = 3 # train a model with same setting N times

def cat_to_ont_hot(dataSet, cat_vars=['Type 1', 'Type 2']):
    train = dataSet.copy()
    for var in cat_vars:
        cat_list='var'+'_'+var
        cat_list = pd.get_dummies(train[var], prefix=var)
        data=train.join(cat_list)
        train=data

    data_vars=train.columns.values.tolist()
    to_keep=[i for i in data_vars if i not in cat_vars]

    return train[to_keep]

def preprocess_data(data=pokemons):
    train, val = train_test_split(data, test_size=0.2, random_state=4211)

    train = cat_to_ont_hot(train)
    val = cat_to_ont_hot(val)

    val.insert(30, 'Type 2_Bug', np.zeros_like(val['Name']))
    val.insert(33, 'Type 2_Electric', np.zeros_like(val['Name']))
    
    return (train, val)

def report(models, size=model_sample_size, needGraph=False, xaxis=[1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64]):
    accuracies = []
    f1_scores = []
    for i in range(0, len(models), size):
        
        time_model, acc_model, f1_model = None, None, None
        best_time, best_acc, best_f1 = 0.0, 0.0, 0.0
        scope = np.arange(size)

        # arrays containing each statistics
        training_time = [models[i + j]['time'] for j in scope]
        accuracy = [(accuracy_score(y_val, models[i + j]['clf'].predict(X_val))) for j in scope]
        f1 =       [(      f1_score(y_val, models[i + j]['clf'].predict(X_val))) for j in scope]
        
        accuracies.append(np.mean(accuracy))
        f1_scores.append(np.mean(f1))

        if np.mean(training_time) > best_time:
            best_time = np.mean(training_time)
            time_model = models[i]
        if np.mean(accuracy) > best_acc:
            best_acc = np.mean(accuracy)
            acc_model = models[i]
        if np.mean(f1) > best_f1:
            best_f1 = np.mean(f1)
            f1_model = models[i]

        print('\n%d / %d' % (i, len(models)))
        print('Model Settings: ', models[i]['clf'])
        print('Mean Training Time: ', np.mean(training_time))
        print('SD of Training Time: ', np.std(training_time))
        print('Mean Accuracy: ', np.mean(accuracy))
        print('SD of Accuracy: ', np.std(accuracy))
        print('Mean F1 score: ', np.mean(f1))
        print('SD of F1 score: ', np.std(f1))
        
    if needGraph:
        plt.plot(xaxis, accuracies, label='accuracy')
        plt.plot(xaxis, f1_scores, label='f1 score')
        plt.xlabel('Hidden Units')
        plt.ylabel('Score')
        plt.legend()
        plt.savefig('tmp.png')
        
    print('\nBest Training Time; ', best_time)
    print(time_model)

    print('\nBest accuracy: ', best_acc)
    print(acc_model)

    print('\nBest f1 score: ', best_f1)
    print(f1_model)

# data pre-processing
train, val = preprocess_data()

X_train = train.drop(['#', 'Name', 'Legendary', 'WinRate'], axis=1)
y_train = train.Legendary

X_val = val.drop(['#', 'Name', 'Legendary', 'WinRate'], axis=1)
y_val = val.Legendary

# hyperparameters combinations
learning_rates = [1e-4, 1e-3, 1e-2, 1e-1]
learning_schedules = ['constant', 'optimal', 'invscaling', 'adaptive']
iterations = [50, 100, 200, 500]

models = []

for it in iterations:
    for lr in learning_rates:
        for ls in learning_schedules:
            for i in np.arange(model_sample_size): # train N times for every settings
                model = {}
                clf = SGDClassifier(loss='log', alpha=lr, learning_rate=ls, eta0=lr, max_iter=it, random_state=0, verbose=1)
                start_time = time.time()
                clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
                model['time'] = time.time() - start_time
                model['clf'] = clf
                models.append(model)
                print("--- training time %s seconds ---" % (model['time']))

# Process the data, we will use all the features of the pokemon

def preprocess_data_task4(battles):
    pokemons = pd.read_csv('./data/pokemon.csv', sep=',')

    train = cat_to_ont_hot(pokemons)
    
    # link 'Second_pokemon' in battle to pokemon list
    first_result = pd.merge(train, battles, left_on='#', right_on='Second_pokemon')
    # Link 'First_pokemon' in battle to pokemon list
    result = pd.merge(train, first_result, left_on='#', right_on='First_pokemon', suffixes=('_First', '_Second'))
    # Change value of 'Winner' to 1 / 0, indicating the current pokemon win / loss
    result['Win'] = (result['Winner'] == result['#_First']) * 1
    # Drop all the unwanted features
